com.vijfhart.casus.tree

Class AbstractNode<T extends AbstractNode<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vijfhart.casus.tree.AbstractNode<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - a subtype of AbstractNode: the actual node type to work with.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    LevelComparable<T>, Node<T>, java.lang.Comparable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NameNode, WrapperNode

    public abstract class AbstractNode<T extends AbstractNode<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Node<T>
    An abstract implementation of Node. This class has an implementation of setParent and isLeaf, and it implements LevelComparable.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(T other)
        Used to determine the position of this Node in the tree. The following rules are used to determine the position of a node: a node without a parent comes first the following node is a child node if that node has child nodes, these nodes will follow, otherwise, the other child nodes of the parent node will follow.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<T extends AbstractNode<T>>
        Parameters:
        other: - the other node
        Returns:
        a negative int if this comes before other, a positive int if this comes after other, otherwise zero.
